<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 05 at 5:22PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Monroe and
northeastern Arkansas Counties through 545 PM CDT...
At 522 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Almyra, or 12 miles southeast of Stuttgart, moving northeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Holly Grove...                    Almyra...
De Witt...                        Aberdeen...
Almyra Airport...                 Casscoe...
Crocketts Bluff...                Lawrenceville...
Duncan...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
